main event: Military personnel observed two unidentified fast-moving objects near Okinawa, which were tracked visually and by radar on June 3, 1953.
interesting points: The objects were estimated to be moving at a speed of approximately 1300 MPH., The sighting lasted for about 13 minutes., Physical evidence was reported, though details were not provided., The course of the objects was from South to North., The report concluded that the radar tracking might have caused optical illusions.
witness description: military personnel stationed at the air bases
